The paper deals with social choice theory, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The algorithm presented in the paper involves checking preference profiles, which is a task that can be automated using artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The empirical and theoretical analysis of the probability of level-1 consensus involves statistical and machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the stability of social choice, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS) and social networks (cs.SI).
